Set up:
With two players, take out the jokers and shuffle the cards.
Give yourself and your opponent 26 faced down cards each.
Each players respective 26 cards is now their deck.
Place your deck in front of you, and your partner must do the same with their deck.
both you and your opponent canâ€™t see either of the decks.
Ace is the highest card.
2 is the lowest card of the game.
Game rules:
Count to 3:
flip the top card at the same time.
Compare the number on the cards.
if your card is higher:
  then you take both cards and put it on the bottom of your deck, winning the round.
else if your opponent has the higher card:
  then he takes both cards and puts it on his deck, winning the round.
else:
  while top showing card is the same :
    then you place 4 faced down card on the table then flip the next top card on the table.
    The one with the highest card takes all the cards and puts it on the bottom of the deck.
If you run out of cards:
  then you lose the game.
else if your opponent runs out of cards:
  then you win the game.
